DESCRIPTION
-----------

Scripts to extract MOSES out of OpenCog project, and replace GPL
license by Apache (MOSES has double licensing).

Extraction
----------

To extract MOSES from OpenCog use the script OC2MOSES.sh. The usage is

./OC2MOSES.sh MOSES_DIR

OC_PATH must be the path of the OpenCog project. MOSES_DIR is the name
of the directory to create and put the MOSES project under. For
example

$ ./OC2MOSES.sh ~/OpenCog/opencog/ moses-3.0.9

It will create a directory moses-3.0.9 with a standalone version of
MOSES under.

Installation
------------

Enter that directory for the next steps to compile and install MOSES
are

$ cd moses-3.0.9

To compile, from the root directory of MOSES:

$ mkdir bin
$ cd bin
$ cmake ..
$ make

Install (may required root privilege)

# make install
# ldconfig
